               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18720506-name-218" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18720506-name-218" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18720506-name-218" type="surname" value="SECKER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18720506-name-218" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM SECKER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a waiter, and live at 31, Hermes Street, Penton<lb></lb>ville—on 1st May, about 12.30 a.m., I was between the Angel and Penton Street, going home—four men set upon me and rifled my pockets—I kept my hand in one pocket—I lost 3<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., I called "Police!"—the police caught the prisoner, and I recognised him as the one in front of me who knocked me down—I cannot tell which of them took the money—they ran away, and the prisoner was brought back by two policemen—I knew him by his face, he was close to me.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I am guilty of being with the others but I did not touch you, and when they ran away I ran away. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> You were right in front of me, and you all put hands on me.</p>
